dharana conists of three faculties

Thus we will be able to advance three principles here as universal,
merely formal or logical criteria of truth; these are

1. The principles of contradiction and of identity,
through which the internal possibility of a cognition is
determined through for problematic judgments

Nirodha Parinama

2. The principle of sufficient reason on which rests
the actuality of a cognition, the fact that it is grounded,
as material for assertoric judgments

Samadhi Parinama

3. The principle of the excluded middle,
on which the logical necessity of a cognition is grounded -
that we must necessarily judge thus and not otherwise,
that the opposite is false - for apodectic judgments

Ekagrata Parinama
